The meeting took place in the cargo bay (the other meeting rooms were
not large enough to accommodate Tigon).  The captain set up some
crates as chairs and one as a table.

&quot;Ok, here&#39;s the situation.  I think we can safely assume that our
repair bot friend is long gone since he hasn&#39;t showed his face in
quite a while.  Here&#39;s the crew roster as it stands now:

Me
Tigon
Betaspiel

We have 4 healthy prisoners, 2 are too dangerous to be let out, 2 can
be used for labor, right?&quot;

&quot;Yes, I am certain that the two you are referring to absolutely 
cannot be released, for any reason.  But actually we have about 14
incarcerated.  I have confirmed 3 of those dead, and 5 of those
missing.  The rest are in stasis.  Continue&quot;

&quot;Right, we have 5 crewmen in stasis, 3 confirmed dead.  That leaves 13
missing.  But that&#39;s not important now.  We need to focus our repair
work, also it would be a good idea to get some more information about
the area around the ship.

I know it&#39;s been easy to just spend all our time doing our own thing,
but I think its time we act like a crew again.

Any questions? ideas?  anything?!?!?!&quot;

Tigon and Betaspeil shook their heads.

&quot;Ok, lets start by repairing the bridge.  I know we don&#39;t&#39; have a lot
of technical skills amongst the three of us, but these repairs are
long overdue.

Dismissed&quot;


